      <section eId="sec_CHC-958">
        <num>CHC 958</num>
        <heading>Section </heading>
        <subsection eId="CHC-958__subsec_A">
          <num>A.</num>
          <content>
            <p>In cases of traffic violations, the court or juvenile traffic referee may dispense with a predisposition investigation and enter a judgment of disposition immediately following adjudication if there is sufficient information in the record to enable the court or referee to determine a fair and just disposition of the case.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CHC-958__subsec_B">
          <num>B.</num>
          <content>
            <p>Judgments of disposition in traffic cases may be evidenced by a minute entry.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=73524</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
